      <bioghist id="aspace_6379d135175b0fadbf56825038b4c82b">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The Valentine family were a prominent family on Long Island since at least the early 19th century. In 1801, William Valentine acquired two paper mills in Roslyn, which the Valentine family controlled for the next century. They also figured prominently in the history of Oyster Bay, Glen Cove, and Hempstead. Alan C. Valentine was chosen to be president of the University of Rochester at age 33.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_a356a3111f5182054dba4899301e1349">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Legal and financial papers concerning the Valentine and related families from Oyster Bay, Glen Cove and Hempstead on Long Island, N.Y. The related families are Bennet, Carpenter, Coles, Mudge, Seamans, Shaw, Titus and Townsend. Among the items are the receipt book for William Bennet's estate (1786-1801), deeds, marriage certificates and wills.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_5765cda0b43ea75907d89ab92f451bea">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The collection is open for research.</p>  
